text: Creully sur Seulles is a commune. It is found in the region Normandy in the Calvados department in the northwest of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2017 and consists of the former communes of Creully (the seat), Saint-Gabriel-Brécy and Villiers-le-Sec.Arrêté préfectoral 8 September 2016 == Related pages == * Communes of the Calvados department == References == Category:2017 establishments in France Category:Communes in Calvados
title: Creully sur Seulles
